      <section eId="sec_CCP-642">
        <num>CCP 642</num>
        <heading>642. Â Determination by court whenever joinder not feasible</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-642__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>To what extent a judgment rendered in the person's absence might be prejudicial to him or those already present.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-642__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The extent to which the prejudice can be lessened or avoided by protective provisions in the judgment, by the shaping of relief, or by other measures.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-642__subsec_3">
          <num>(3)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Whether a judgment rendered in the person's absence will be adequate.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-642__subsec_4">
          <num>(4)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Whether the plaintiff will have an adequate remedy if the action is dismissed for nonjoinder.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112201</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
